    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Well, I had a look at #17257 before reporting this. IMHO, they are not related: there, it's the `merge()` method itself that shows unexpected behaviour, while here, some helper method of `join()` simply calls `merge()` with the wrong argument `how='outer'`. If `merge()` had been called correctly using `how='left'`, everything would be fine. \r\n\r\nSeems easy to fix, but might break existing code. I will look into how to fix it.."
